<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,506,843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">
Diagnosis. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Chen" authorityName="Chen &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2017" box="[634,937,611,635]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Niwaella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrolinea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[634,777,611,635]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">N. nigrolinea</emphasis>
Chen &amp; Chen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[949,1037,611,635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[949,1037,611,635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in color pattern, but differs by having 19–20 large, conspicuous blotches on the dorsum (vs. 19–22 small, inconspicuous blotches); suborbital spine straight, with short processus latero-caudalis, less than one-fifth of processus medio-caudalis (vs. suborbital spine curved, with long processus latero-caudalis, less than one-third of processus medio-caudalis); caudal peduncle short, length of caudal peduncle 6.5–7.5 (mean 7.0) in SL (vs. caudal peduncle long, length of caudal peduncle 5.8–6.8 (mean 6.2) in SL); body sturdy, depth 8.3–8.5 (mean 8.4) in SL (vs. slender, depth 9.4–10.6 (mean 9.8) in SL); subdorsal scales with a small focal area (vs. a large focal area).
</paragraph>
